Lupinus albifrons is a species of flowering plant in the legume family, Fabaceae. 
It is commonly known as the Silver lupine or White-leaf bush lupine. 
The plant is native to western North America, particularly California and Oregon. 
It is a perennial herb that grows up to 1 meter tall. 
Lupinus albifrons has silvery-green leaves that are palmately compound. 
The flowers are white with a touch of blue, and form a spike that blooms from late spring to early summer. 
The plant is commonly found in dry coastal and inland hillsides, grasslands, and forests.
